Date: Fri, 06 Aug 1999 17:31:23 -0500
From: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj@mail.vetmed.lsu.edu>
Source: OIE Weekly Report; 6 August 1999 Vol. 12 - No. 30

(Date of last previously reported outbreak: November 1979)
Emergency report
Text of a fax received on 2 August 1999 from Dr Celal Özcan, General
Director of Protection and Control, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural
Affairs, Ankara:
Report date: 2 August 1999.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 26 July 1999.
Estimated date of first infection: 20 July 1999.
Outbreaks:
Location No. of outbreaks
Vaysal village, 1
Lâlapa district,
Edirne province
(in the north-western part of the country)
Description of affected population:
Sheep reared on pasture along the border with Bulgaria.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species ovine
susceptible 600
cases 5
deaths 0
destroyed 0
slaughtered 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Etlik Central Veterinary Control
and Research Institute.
B. Diagnostic tests used: competitive ELISA. Virus isolation is in progress.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
B. Mode of spread: insect-borne infection.
Control measures during reporting period:
- control of arthropods;
- control of wildlife reservoirs;
- quarantine and movement control inside the country;
- vaccination.
--
ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
